            <V n="text" t="variation">
              <U n="variation">
                <L n="variations">
                  <T>0x4B8BF986<!--If you stop by the Baleful Bog, you can temporarily become a Ghost. I've got a pet Death Frog for a similar reason, though I confess: it makes me feel a little odd to merely pretend to be a ghost. My motto as a musician is that if you're gonna go for it, you should go all the way! --></T>
                  <T>0xCD019BE8<!--Can you believe that when Olive and I first met up—at the cemetery, naturally—she had no idea I'm a musician? It was refreshing to run into someone who doesn't know you before they know you.--></T>
                  <T>0x411392F6<!--I've always felt a strange pull towards death. It never felt right to admit, but what I was drawn towards wasn't just the, well, grim idea of death so much as the potency of seeing a spectrum of existence around it. There's an event, Celebration of Life, that happens in Crow's Crossing sometimes. I'll visit to get a taste of the other side of death; the moment when the living gather to bask in remembrances of you.--></T>
                </L>
              </U>
